1
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:45,963
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

2
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:49,550
I look forward to working with you,
Ms. Shin Seo-ri.

3
00:01:00,811 --> 00:01:03,355
Deal sealed.

4
00:01:07,484 --> 00:01:08,819
Damn it.

5
00:01:12,239 --> 00:01:13,532
Sir.

6
00:01:17,077 --> 00:01:19,913
What in the world is going on?

7
00:01:19,997 --> 00:01:23,000
It means I'm buying your company
with my pocket money.

8
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:24,710
Mr. Son, perfect timing.

9
00:01:24,793 --> 00:01:26,211
You'll need to clean this up.

10
00:01:26,295 --> 00:01:29,172
I just made them an offer
they can't refuse.

11
00:01:30,257 --> 00:01:32,426
- Sir, not again…
- Yes, that's right.

12
00:01:33,093 --> 00:01:36,054
It's exactly what you're thinking.

13
00:01:37,848 --> 00:01:39,725
Mr. Son, you take care of them.

14
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:43,103
Please follow me.

15
00:01:44,438 --> 00:01:45,981
Ms. Shin, you come this way.

16
00:01:48,483 --> 00:01:49,818
Which way?

17
00:01:52,654 --> 00:01:53,655
Here.

18
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:55,699
Towards me.

19
00:02:03,874 --> 00:02:06,084
Why does he keep smiling?

20
00:02:07,002 --> 00:02:08,670
A man should not be so frivolous.

21
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:24,311
EPISODE 4
BEYOND UNDERSTANDING

22
00:02:38,450 --> 00:02:40,285
I can't stand looking at your red face.

23
00:02:40,369 --> 00:02:41,870
Do something about it.

24
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:45,791
What? No.
I didn't mean for you to drink it.

25
00:02:48,043 --> 00:02:49,795
Cha Se-gye, speak plainly.

26
00:02:49,878 --> 00:02:50,837
What are you scheming?

27
00:02:50,921 --> 00:02:52,839
What now? What's your problem?

28
00:02:52,923 --> 00:02:53,965
Given the situation,

29
00:02:54,049 --> 00:02:57,135
this contract business seems to be
anything but simple.

30
00:02:57,219 --> 00:02:58,345
I am no fool.

31
00:02:58,929 --> 00:03:00,597
You have sense, but no shame.

32
00:03:00,681 --> 00:03:02,849
If anything, you should be
on your knees thanking me.

33
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:05,352
You can't afford
to be talking to me like this.

34
00:03:05,435 --> 00:03:07,521
Bow down to you? What utter nonsense.

35
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:11,441
I have never bowed down
to anyone in my entire life.

36
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:16,905
No wonder you're still an unknown actress.

37
00:03:16,988 --> 00:03:19,324
I'm only saying this once, so listen up.

38
00:03:19,408 --> 00:03:21,034
The first law of investment.

39
00:03:21,118 --> 00:03:23,578
Buy on fear, sell on hype.

40
00:03:23,662 --> 00:03:26,289
I'm buying you at the lower limit,
just before delisting,

41
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:28,750
so I can sell you off at the peak.

42
00:03:28,834 --> 00:03:30,961
Sell me? Are you saying
you're going to traffic me?

43
00:03:31,044 --> 00:03:33,672
Not trafficking. Investing.

44
00:03:34,339 --> 00:03:35,799
Investing, you say?

45
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:41,888
In other words,
you intend to bet big on my potential.

46
00:03:42,431 --> 00:03:43,640
Is that what you mean?

47
00:03:43,724 --> 00:03:45,142
More or less.

48
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:46,893
You could have just said that.

49
00:03:46,977 --> 00:03:47,978
Why talk in circles?

50
00:03:52,023 --> 00:03:54,651
Now I finally see why you possess
such an obstinate spirit.

51
00:03:54,735 --> 00:03:58,405
You have blocked out the sun.
No wonder you are bitter and twisted.

52
00:04:00,699 --> 00:04:04,161
Just look at that wide open view.
Is it not the most refreshing?

53
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:06,204
What are you doing? Someone might see.

54
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:22,304
"Vast heavens, precious earth."

55
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:25,474
Your spirit grows cold
because you turn from such precious light.

56
00:04:25,557 --> 00:04:28,101
Some of us have no windows
and stare at walls all day.

57
00:04:28,185 --> 00:04:29,478
You take it for granted.

58
00:04:30,437 --> 00:04:31,855
You have no windows at home?

59
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:36,526
I do, but it is a window
in name only. That is the issue.

60
00:04:38,403 --> 00:04:40,822
Enough about the windows.
We're done here.

61
00:04:40,906 --> 00:04:42,574
Shouldn't you be going now?

62
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:44,034
I was just leaving.

63
00:04:45,786 --> 00:04:46,661
Unbelievable.

64
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:57,631
That man blows hot and cold.

65
00:04:58,340 --> 00:04:59,800
I mean, he beckons me to follow,

66
00:04:59,883 --> 00:05:02,719
and then he casts me aside
the moment he is done with me.

67
00:05:10,101 --> 00:05:11,102
Oh no.

68
00:05:11,186 --> 00:05:13,647
When did this get so swollen?

69
00:05:19,402 --> 00:05:22,197
I can't stand that bright red face.
Do something about it.

70
00:05:29,412 --> 00:05:31,498
He did not give it to me to drink.

71
00:05:31,581 --> 00:05:33,458
He gave it to me to rub on my face.

72
00:05:35,669 --> 00:05:38,880
That Cha Se-gye. He is so uselessly soft.

73
00:05:44,219 --> 00:05:45,345
Why did I do that?

74
00:05:45,971 --> 00:05:48,473
Why did I make
such a reckless, unplanned move?

75
00:05:48,557 --> 00:05:51,351
Did that weird dream break my brain?

76
00:05:51,434 --> 00:05:54,396
Then again, a meticulous planner like you
would never go off track.

77
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:57,732
That is, unless you've fallen in love.

78
00:05:57,816 --> 00:05:59,442
Me? With a crazy woman like that?

79
00:05:59,526 --> 00:06:01,403
Not unless I'm dead and buried
in the dirt.

80
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:03,655
- Did some dirt get in your eye?
- Damn it.

81
00:06:03,738 --> 00:06:05,282
Shall I get you some eye drops?

82
00:06:05,365 --> 00:06:07,075
What? When did you get here?

83
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:09,327
I've been here since Ms. Shin left.

84
00:06:09,411 --> 00:06:12,289
Are you a hitman or something?
I can't even hear you breathe.

85
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:14,291
You said my breathing bothered you,

86
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:16,376
so I honed this skill.
Zero-gravity breathing.

87
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:22,632
So?

88
00:06:24,384 --> 00:06:25,260
What did you hear?

89
00:06:25,343 --> 00:06:26,469
"Is my brain broken?"

90
00:06:26,553 --> 00:06:28,448
"With a crazy woman like that?"

91
00:06:28,504 --> 00:06:29,973
"Maybe when I'm dead…"

92
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:31,391
That's enough.

93
00:06:31,466 --> 00:06:33,852
I think this situation could be
quite easily misconstrued.

94
00:06:33,935 --> 00:06:35,687
You have to read between the lines.

95
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:37,522
I don't let things

96
00:06:37,606 --> 00:06:39,983
like compassion or pity sway me.

97
00:06:40,066 --> 00:06:42,110
I am no humanist
when it comes to business.

98
00:06:42,193 --> 00:06:44,821
Yes, I'm already aware of that.

99
00:06:44,905 --> 00:06:46,531
After that rear-end collision last year,

100
00:06:46,615 --> 00:06:49,075
you had me working all night
with casts on both legs.

101
00:06:49,159 --> 00:06:50,035
Wow.

102
00:06:50,118 --> 00:06:52,454
No one with a shred
of humanity could do that.

103
00:06:52,537 --> 00:06:54,831
- I understood then.
- Okay, you can leave now.

104
00:07:09,554 --> 00:07:11,389
Just a few slaps to the face,

105
00:07:11,932 --> 00:07:14,684
and I'm acting like some forlorn stray
caught in the rain.

106
00:07:15,602 --> 00:07:16,770
What a fool.

107
00:07:22,317 --> 00:07:23,318
Go away.

108
00:07:23,401 --> 00:07:24,319
Shoo.

109
00:07:28,031 --> 00:07:29,115
Shoo. Go.

110
00:07:30,241 --> 00:07:31,201
Go to your owner.

111
00:07:31,743 --> 00:07:32,827
Shoo.

112
00:07:33,411 --> 00:07:35,747
By the looks of you, you must be homeless.

113
00:07:36,748 --> 00:07:37,916
So am I.

114
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:40,085
Clinging to me is pointless.

115
00:07:48,802 --> 00:07:49,678
Hey, dog.

116
00:07:50,428 --> 00:07:51,388
Stop following me.

117
00:07:53,223 --> 00:07:54,474
You are not wanted here.

118
00:07:57,936 --> 00:07:58,853
Jeez.

119
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,193
Go away!

120
00:08:07,904 --> 00:08:09,698
No, I did not ask you to fetch.

121
00:08:15,370 --> 00:08:17,247
Why are you so clingy?

122
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:19,624
DAEBAK BOARDING HOUSE

123
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:21,710
Windfall luck was never in my fate.

124
00:08:23,795 --> 00:08:27,132
I may possess exceptional talents
and striking looks,

125
00:08:27,632 --> 00:08:30,135
but the winds have been too favorable.

126
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:33,722
Yes, windfalls that blow in without effort

127
00:08:33,805 --> 00:08:35,557
are bound to blow back.

128
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:37,475
He may call it an "investment,"

129
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:40,645
but that obstinate man
must still want something from me.

130
00:08:40,729 --> 00:08:42,480
Why else would he be such a sucker?

131
00:08:45,692 --> 00:08:48,486
Jeez, you're always watching dramas.

132
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:51,114
If you put that drive to good use,
you'd already be employed.

133
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:53,700
Why are you nagging me?
Even my mom doesn't do that.

134
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:55,535
Even job seekers need room to breathe.

135
00:08:55,618 --> 00:08:58,997
I have never once seen you studying.

136
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:01,666
Are you a fan of Yoon Ji-hyo or something?

137
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:03,668
Are you a Yoon Ji-hyo fan too?

138
00:09:03,752 --> 00:09:04,878
A fan?

139
00:09:04,961 --> 00:09:06,880
Silently rooting for them makes you a fan.

140
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:09,841
You wish them well, worry about them,
and send them gifts.

141
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:14,387
Of course. He must be my fan.

142
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:16,973
So the beef was a tribute offering.

143
00:09:18,141 --> 00:09:19,684
My good man.

144
00:09:19,768 --> 00:09:21,686
Are these so-called fans

145
00:09:21,770 --> 00:09:23,563
like guardian angels?

146
00:09:23,646 --> 00:09:25,565
Always worrying about useless things,

147
00:09:25,648 --> 00:09:28,193
wishing you well, and taking your side?

148
00:09:28,818 --> 00:09:29,986
Guardian angels?

149
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:32,155
Well, that's basically what it means.

150
00:09:32,238 --> 00:09:35,325
Then what should I do for this fan?

151
00:09:35,408 --> 00:09:38,536
Why do anything?
Your existence alone is a gift to them.

152
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:41,748
They offer such kindness
and expect nothing in return?

153
00:09:41,831 --> 00:09:44,417
No, that's not it. These days,

154
00:09:44,501 --> 00:09:46,377
stars give back to their fans.

155
00:09:46,461 --> 00:09:48,213
They call it a "gift in return."

156
00:09:48,296 --> 00:09:49,506
- Gift…
- A gift in return.

157
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:50,590
A gift in return.

158
00:09:50,673 --> 00:09:52,592
Then again, even our Lady Ji-hyo

159
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:54,302
buys her fans luxury goods

160
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:56,054
and writes them letters by hand.

161
00:09:57,055 --> 00:09:58,098
Luxury goods?

162
00:09:58,890 --> 00:10:00,100
Handwritten letters…

163
00:10:01,142 --> 00:10:04,521
So this… "gift in return" business.

164
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:06,356
What else does it entail?

165
00:10:06,439 --> 00:10:09,025
Using the launch of Dynaestie
as a stepping stone,

166
00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:11,694
Biojei has decided to acquire
Shin Seo-ri's talent agency.

167
00:10:11,778 --> 00:10:14,322
An anonymous company poll
on Ms. Shin Seo-ri's public image

168
00:10:14,405 --> 00:10:16,449
showed a positive response.

169
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:18,576
So there were no major objections,

170
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:19,994
but the funding is a concern.

171
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:23,039
The Kaiserman issue
also remains unresolved.

172
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:26,376
Don't worry about that.
I'll find a way to handle it.

173
00:10:31,881 --> 00:10:34,300
What are you doing here?
You never come to my fishing spot.

174
00:10:34,384 --> 00:10:37,095
That's a bit harsh to say
to your only grandson.

175
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:39,472
Coming here on your own, unannounced,

176
00:10:39,556 --> 00:10:42,016
must mean you come
with ulterior motives. Am I wrong?

177
00:10:42,100 --> 00:10:43,893
Okay, I'll be frank, Grandfather.

178
00:10:43,977 --> 00:10:46,062
I need a loan against my trust fund.

179
00:10:46,771 --> 00:10:50,775
You ask for money so easily,
as if you're owed it?

180
00:10:50,859 --> 00:10:52,068
You think money is easy?

181
00:10:52,152 --> 00:10:54,612
If it were that easy,
I wouldn't look so defeated.

182
00:10:55,113 --> 00:10:56,698
I've given this a lot of thought.

183
00:10:56,781 --> 00:10:58,449
Yes, Attorney Choi told me

184
00:10:58,533 --> 00:11:01,119
you borrowed investment money
from Mun-do.

185
00:11:01,202 --> 00:11:04,164
You need quick cash
if you're starting a new business.

186
00:11:05,290 --> 00:11:08,209
When it comes to backing,
nothing beats the Bank of Grandpa.

187
00:11:08,293 --> 00:11:09,627
It won't be free money, punk.

188
00:11:09,711 --> 00:11:12,881
Did you ever see me make
a losing deal, even with family?

189
00:11:12,964 --> 00:11:14,591
What do you want this time?

190
00:11:15,675 --> 00:11:17,510
Let's go. I'll buy you a nice dinner.

191
00:11:17,594 --> 00:11:19,971
You think you can
just buy me off with a meal?

192
00:11:20,054 --> 00:11:21,139
Forget it.

193
00:11:21,222 --> 00:11:22,599
I have somewhere else to be.

194
00:11:22,682 --> 00:11:24,760
JINMI JANGSUGOL PORK BACKBONE STEW

195
00:11:24,859 --> 00:11:26,228
Gosh, this place is packed today.

196
00:11:26,303 --> 00:11:27,878
It's full, Chairman Cha. Wait out there.

197
00:11:27,989 --> 00:11:29,647
No perks for a 40-year regular?

198
00:11:29,731 --> 00:11:32,442
I've been buying your soup
since your shantytown days.

199
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:34,652
It doesn't matter
if you're a 40-year regular or a CEO.

200
00:11:34,736 --> 00:11:35,987
Here, there's one rule.

201
00:11:36,070 --> 00:11:38,198
Everyone waits in the same line.
Now get out.

202
00:11:38,281 --> 00:11:39,908
You're one stubborn old lady.

203
00:11:39,991 --> 00:11:42,160
It's just that I don't have time today.

204
00:11:42,243 --> 00:11:43,578
My goodness.

205
00:11:44,704 --> 00:11:47,207
Hey, what about sharing
a table with someone?

206
00:11:47,290 --> 00:11:48,833
That young lady is by herself.

207
00:11:51,669 --> 00:11:54,964
As if kids these days
share tables with old geezers!

208
00:11:56,591 --> 00:11:57,884
Hold on.

209
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:01,930
Excuse me, miss.
There aren't any seats left, you see.

210
00:12:02,013 --> 00:12:03,640
Could I possibly join you?

211
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:05,642
I'm almost done. Please wait.

212
00:12:05,725 --> 00:12:09,229
I'm just a little short on time, you see.
Just help me out here.

213
00:12:09,312 --> 00:12:11,231
Then you should have timed it better.

214
00:12:11,314 --> 00:12:13,942
- Good grief. I do not owe you a seat.
- Well, then…

215
00:12:14,025 --> 00:12:17,111
I'll pay for your meal, miss.

216
00:12:17,195 --> 00:12:18,196
How about it?

217
00:12:24,827 --> 00:12:26,496
Deal sealed.

218
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:43,846
That wide open view.
Is it not the most refreshing?

219
00:12:43,930 --> 00:12:46,474
Some of us have no windows
and stare at walls all day.

220
00:12:46,557 --> 00:12:47,767
You take it for granted.

221
00:12:49,352 --> 00:12:52,272
Mr. Son, are there still apartments
without windows these days?

222
00:12:52,355 --> 00:12:53,815
I mean, don't you need windows

223
00:12:53,898 --> 00:12:55,483
to get a building permit?

224
00:12:55,566 --> 00:12:56,859
It could be built illegally.

225
00:12:56,943 --> 00:12:58,987
Cheap rentals and boarding houses
might not have them.

226
00:12:59,070 --> 00:13:00,363
Really? No windows?

227
00:13:00,446 --> 00:13:03,283
So, a window that opens
to face a wall is also possible?

228
00:13:03,866 --> 00:13:05,159
Usually, in a boarding house,

229
00:13:05,243 --> 00:13:07,203
windows, bathrooms, and refrigerators

230
00:13:07,287 --> 00:13:09,163
are all considered amenities.

231
00:13:09,247 --> 00:13:11,499
I guess the cheapest rooms
wouldn't have them.

232
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:14,544
Why the sudden interest?

233
00:13:15,295 --> 00:13:18,631
Oh, I was just passing by a TV
playing Screening Humanity.

234
00:13:18,715 --> 00:13:19,841
I see…

235
00:13:27,557 --> 00:13:30,935
Why is a young person like you
eating soup all by yourself?

236
00:13:31,019 --> 00:13:32,395
I prefer being alone.

237
00:13:32,478 --> 00:13:34,564
Nothing to grate on my nerves either.

238
00:13:34,981 --> 00:13:35,940
That's true.

239
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:43,281
Hold on.

240
00:13:45,450 --> 00:13:47,118
Judging by his facial features,

241
00:13:47,201 --> 00:13:50,496
his disposition is petty
and insufferably thin-skinned,

242
00:13:51,122 --> 00:13:53,291
but he has a "hanging gallbladder" nose.

243
00:13:53,374 --> 00:13:55,168
His coffers are generously lined.

244
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:57,628
He is blessed with wealth
and ample provisions.

245
00:13:57,712 --> 00:13:59,672
The classic face of a man
of immense means.

246
00:13:59,756 --> 00:14:00,882
In that case…

247
00:14:00,965 --> 00:14:02,050
Excuse me, mistress!

248
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:04,427
- One seafood pancake, please.
- Right away.

249
00:14:04,927 --> 00:14:07,263
Miss, why did you order that?

250
00:14:07,347 --> 00:14:10,183
I was just thinking,
and I realized suppertime is upon us.

251
00:14:10,808 --> 00:14:13,269
Peak evening hours,
when establishments are at their busiest.

252
00:14:13,353 --> 00:14:16,356
You are bound to wait anywhere you go,
yet you secured this table with ease.

253
00:14:16,439 --> 00:14:18,816
So adding a pancake should make it even.

254
00:14:19,359 --> 00:14:20,735
Do you not agree?

255
00:14:22,695 --> 00:14:25,740
It does feel like I'm fleeced
with my eyes wide open,

256
00:14:25,823 --> 00:14:28,701
- but sure. Why not?
- Do not worry. I will share half.

257
00:14:29,369 --> 00:14:30,787
Oh, right.

258
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:33,373
- One more thing, while we are at it.
- What now?

259
00:14:37,418 --> 00:14:40,213
What are you going to do
with these leftover bones?

260
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:42,340
I have an important use for them.

261
00:14:43,883 --> 00:14:45,760
You know, I'm known for being frugal,

262
00:14:45,843 --> 00:14:48,471
but you're really something else, miss.

263
00:14:48,554 --> 00:14:50,390
You'll never starve, that's for sure.

264
00:14:50,473 --> 00:14:52,350
I get that a lot.

265
00:14:52,975 --> 00:14:54,727
Thanks to you, I ate very well.

266
00:14:55,228 --> 00:14:56,604
Take care.

267
00:14:58,981 --> 00:15:00,733
A free meal and free bones.

268
00:15:00,817 --> 00:15:03,111
She really got her money's worth.

269
00:15:10,785 --> 00:15:13,413
Hey! Come here, Doggy! Spot! Scruffy!

270
00:15:13,496 --> 00:15:15,164
Rover! Rusty!

271
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:22,422
Where could that dog have gone?
Did it just vanish into thin air?

272
00:15:22,505 --> 00:15:24,090
Did someone already take it?

273
00:15:24,173 --> 00:15:27,677
Whatever.
Who cares if someone took it or not?

274
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,846
My own belly is a prisoner of starvation.

275
00:16:03,671 --> 00:16:04,589
What?

276
00:16:07,216 --> 00:16:08,217
It was you?

277
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:11,137
Dingy little dog. Go on, get away.

278
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:12,889
I guess that is a dog's nose for you.

279
00:16:12,972 --> 00:16:14,348
How did you ever find me?

280
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:23,065
I did not throw this for you to fetch.

281
00:16:23,149 --> 00:16:24,817
I threw it to make you go away.

282
00:16:25,318 --> 00:16:26,736
Silly dog.

283
00:16:31,199 --> 00:16:33,951
Hey, spit that out!
You should not eat things like that.

284
00:16:34,494 --> 00:16:36,829
Are you hungry?

285
00:16:37,330 --> 00:16:38,247
Damn it.

286
00:16:38,331 --> 00:16:40,583
Damn stray dogs and cats.

287
00:16:40,666 --> 00:16:42,668
If I ever catch you, you'll be toast!

288
00:16:42,752 --> 00:16:44,378
- You wait here.
- Just look at this mess!

289
00:16:44,462 --> 00:16:46,005
- I will get you some food.
- Unbelievable.

290
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:47,215
Damn it.

291
00:16:47,882 --> 00:16:49,091
Damn it all.

292
00:16:49,175 --> 00:16:50,927
I hate my life.

293
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:52,053
Jeez.

294
00:16:53,054 --> 00:16:54,430
Seriously?

295
00:16:54,514 --> 00:16:56,098
I can't believe this.

296
00:16:56,182 --> 00:16:58,768
Hey, Unit 203!
Where have you been all day?

297
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:01,812
I was just coming back from a stroll.

298
00:17:01,896 --> 00:17:02,813
What is it?

299
00:17:02,897 --> 00:17:06,359
You put our boarding house's number
on your résumé, didn't you?

300
00:17:06,442 --> 00:17:08,528
The police just called.
It was absolute chaos.

301
00:17:08,611 --> 00:17:09,904
The police station?

302
00:17:10,863 --> 00:17:12,281
The police station?

303
00:17:13,241 --> 00:17:14,283
The police? Why?

304
00:17:14,367 --> 00:17:16,702
The assistant director
from that home shopping channel

305
00:17:16,786 --> 00:17:18,329
filed an assault complaint.

306
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:21,040
I'm calling you after handing it over
to the legal team.

307
00:17:21,123 --> 00:17:22,041
Really?

308
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,293
I'm sure you handled it.

309
00:17:24,377 --> 00:17:27,838
I assume he got a bogus doctor's note
to try and get a big payout.

310
00:17:27,922 --> 00:17:29,507
I'd rather do without cheap rumors.

311
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:31,759
Pay him double what he wants
and just shut him up.

312
00:17:31,842 --> 00:17:34,387
Yes, sir. As a precaution,
I'll ensure Ms. Shin's case

313
00:17:34,470 --> 00:17:35,805
is separated.

314
00:17:36,305 --> 00:17:37,265
Shin Seo-ri?

315
00:17:39,642 --> 00:17:40,810
What about her?

316
00:17:42,019 --> 00:17:44,355
Okay. Everyone needs to calm down.

317
00:17:44,855 --> 00:17:46,315
So, let me get this straight.

318
00:17:46,399 --> 00:17:48,818
You grabbed him, and his arm was injured.

319
00:17:48,901 --> 00:17:51,988
And he refused to pay you your wages.

320
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:54,115
So, we have unpaid wages and assault.

321
00:17:54,198 --> 00:17:56,117
Are you going to sue each other now?

322
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,159
What do you mean?

323
00:17:57,243 --> 00:17:59,954
Her wages have nothing to do with me.
Just the assault.

324
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:03,082
All this fuss over a simple wrist grab?

325
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:06,460
If I had tripped you,
you would probably pretend to be dying.

326
00:18:06,544 --> 00:18:08,546
You are even making this dog laugh.

327
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:12,466
What? Because of you,
I'm about to lose my job.

328
00:18:12,550 --> 00:18:13,509
My medical bills

329
00:18:13,593 --> 00:18:15,761
and emotional distress.
You'll pay for it all!

330
00:18:15,845 --> 00:18:17,805
I thought the compensation was settled.

331
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:21,392
Double the standard settlement

332
00:18:21,934 --> 00:18:23,436
for a six-week injury diagnosis,

333
00:18:23,519 --> 00:18:25,146
generously provided by my legal team.

334
00:18:25,229 --> 00:18:26,897
Was that not enough?

335
00:18:26,981 --> 00:18:28,566
- Who are you?
- Oh, right.

336
00:18:32,278 --> 00:18:33,988
Along with this woman,

337
00:18:34,071 --> 00:18:36,240
I was the other party in his assault case.

338
00:18:37,491 --> 00:18:39,493
I paid a settlement,
so my case was dropped.

339
00:18:39,577 --> 00:18:43,289
Are you saying you paid
to weasel your way out of this?

340
00:18:43,831 --> 00:18:45,082
To leave me high and dry?

341
00:18:45,166 --> 00:18:47,418
That's why it's always
better to have money.

342
00:18:47,501 --> 00:18:49,128
It's not too late to start trying.

343
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:51,797
Although I'm not sure
you'll ever know what it's like.

344
00:18:52,298 --> 00:18:54,342
Hey, you can just stay out of this.

345
00:18:54,425 --> 00:18:57,595
Sir, let's just move this along.
We're all busy, aren't we?

346
00:18:57,678 --> 00:19:00,348
- Yes, let's move this along.
- What?

347
00:19:00,431 --> 00:19:01,682
Please file this as well.

348
00:19:01,766 --> 00:19:03,017
What? Okay.

349
00:19:04,644 --> 00:19:05,936
Let's proceed with a countersuit.

350
00:19:06,020 --> 00:19:07,563
Breach of standard labor contract.

351
00:19:07,647 --> 00:19:10,232
I discovered you were in charge
of managing the extras.

352
00:19:10,316 --> 00:19:11,442
Just like your arm,

353
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:13,944
Ms. Shin suffered severe health issues.

354
00:19:17,823 --> 00:19:20,868
Evidenced by her vomiting live on air,
currently under regulatory review.

355
00:19:20,951 --> 00:19:23,454
And on top of that,
there are unpaid wages.

356
00:19:23,537 --> 00:19:25,915
Should I just sue the entire network?

357
00:19:25,998 --> 00:19:26,874
What?

358
00:19:26,957 --> 00:19:29,001
There's no reason
to blow this up like that.

359
00:19:29,085 --> 00:19:30,836
This is strictly a personal matter.

360
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:32,213
You're right.

361
00:19:32,296 --> 00:19:33,756
So the network's the problem.

362
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:36,217
How about we file a joint lawsuit?

363
00:19:37,093 --> 00:19:40,930
I'm no stranger to either side
of a legal battle.

364
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:53,359
Why you…

365
00:20:00,491 --> 00:20:01,575
Cha Se-gye.

366
00:20:02,284 --> 00:20:04,704
Did you rush over here
because you were worried about me?

367
00:20:04,787 --> 00:20:07,289
No. I didn't come because I was worried.

368
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:11,836
The contractee owes
a duty of care to the contractor.

369
00:20:11,919 --> 00:20:14,255
And this is practically next door

370
00:20:14,797 --> 00:20:16,006
to my place.

371
00:20:16,882 --> 00:20:18,509
"Practically next door"?

372
00:20:19,135 --> 00:20:20,428
I see.

373
00:20:20,928 --> 00:20:22,638
So are we what they call
"neighbor-cousins,"

374
00:20:22,722 --> 00:20:24,932
who can often feel closer to you
than blood relatives?

375
00:20:25,558 --> 00:20:26,809
Neighbor-cousins? As if.

376
00:20:26,892 --> 00:20:29,395
Do you even know the property value gap
between our neighborhoods?

377
00:20:29,478 --> 00:20:31,105
Always with that coy back-and-forth.

378
00:20:31,188 --> 00:20:32,523
I know what is in your heart.

379
00:20:32,606 --> 00:20:35,276
You came because you were worried
and missed me, right?

380
00:20:35,359 --> 00:20:38,571
It's like you make a hobby
of twisting things to make it seem like

381
00:20:38,654 --> 00:20:39,780
I worry about you.

382
00:20:39,864 --> 00:20:40,906
Oh, all right.

383
00:20:41,449 --> 00:20:44,243
It was that coyness that led me
to mistake your true intentions.

384
00:20:44,326 --> 00:20:45,703
I shall not mind it at all.

385
00:20:50,207 --> 00:20:51,751
And what's with the dog?

386
00:20:51,834 --> 00:20:53,043
Just a dog I found.

387
00:20:53,127 --> 00:20:54,044
Don't tell me.

388
00:20:54,712 --> 00:20:56,589
You can't keep it in that windowless room.

389
00:20:56,672 --> 00:20:58,841
- That is no concern of yours.
- Such a busybody.

390
00:20:58,924 --> 00:21:00,259
Dogs are for life, you know.

391
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:02,803
You shouldn't pick up a stray
if you can't commit.

392
00:21:04,013 --> 00:21:06,974
Fine, keep it or don't.
Do whatever you want.

393
00:21:07,057 --> 00:21:10,227
Shin Seo-ri, before we enter
into this contract,

394
00:21:10,311 --> 00:21:11,937
let's set one ground rule first.

395
00:21:12,521 --> 00:21:14,648
- Go on.
- From now on, let's be sure to keep

396
00:21:14,732 --> 00:21:16,817
our professional
and personal lives separate.

397
00:21:16,901 --> 00:21:19,195
Whether by social class or by status,

398
00:21:19,278 --> 00:21:22,281
we have absolutely no business
getting mixed up like this.

399
00:21:22,364 --> 00:21:24,116
That should not be an issue for me.

400
00:21:25,034 --> 00:21:26,076
However,

401
00:21:26,786 --> 00:21:27,953
I am worried about you.

402
00:21:30,039 --> 00:21:33,584
You will be absolutely itching to see me
in a more personal capacity.

403
00:21:33,667 --> 00:21:34,960
Think you can resist?

404
00:21:38,255 --> 00:21:40,841
You know, this conversation took
a mighty wrong turn earlier.

405
00:21:40,925 --> 00:21:42,551
What kind of delusional thought process

406
00:21:42,635 --> 00:21:45,471
leads you to conclude that I'd long
for someone like you?

407
00:21:45,554 --> 00:21:46,931
Then let us do this.

408
00:21:47,014 --> 00:21:49,475
Since you are worried
about this dog living in a room

409
00:21:49,558 --> 00:21:50,643
without windows,

410
00:21:50,726 --> 00:21:53,062
and I wish to give you a gift in return,

411
00:21:53,145 --> 00:21:54,688
we can simply make an exchange.

412
00:21:54,772 --> 00:21:55,898
"Gift in return"?

413
00:21:57,525 --> 00:21:59,568
"Exchange"? You're not making any sense.

414
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:03,656
By any chance,
does that older brother of yours

415
00:22:04,156 --> 00:22:06,617
- visit your home often?
- "Brother"? Who?

416
00:22:08,327 --> 00:22:09,620
Choi Mun-do?

417
00:22:09,703 --> 00:22:11,664
Why the hell would he come to my house?

418
00:22:20,589 --> 00:22:23,926
You know, she just showed up
unfazed with her dog.

419
00:22:24,009 --> 00:22:25,845
I explained to the police

420
00:22:25,928 --> 00:22:28,806
that I planned to claim full compensation,
emotional damages included.

421
00:22:28,889 --> 00:22:29,890
As I was doing that,

422
00:22:29,974 --> 00:22:32,101
Mr. Cha Se-gye showed up,
just as you predicted.

423
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:34,937
He even had the charges
against Shin Seo-ri dropped.

424
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:36,230
Biojei Entertainment?

425
00:22:38,315 --> 00:22:41,277
After recruiting Shin Seo-ri,
an obscure actress, Mr. Cha is looking

426
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:42,820
to acquire her agency as well.

427
00:22:42,903 --> 00:22:46,949
A late-night trip to the police station
and a sudden agency acquisition.

428
00:22:48,117 --> 00:22:48,993
How amusing.

429
00:22:49,076 --> 00:22:51,954
Se-gye keeps creating
more leverage for me all on his own.

430
00:22:52,580 --> 00:22:54,790
Despite being family,
it seems he is not someone

431
00:22:54,874 --> 00:22:56,417
you welcome into your home.

432
00:22:57,626 --> 00:22:58,711
"He"?

433
00:23:02,172 --> 00:23:04,008
Why do you keep asking about Choi Mun-do?

434
00:23:04,091 --> 00:23:06,844
What, is he your type or something?

435
00:23:08,470 --> 00:23:09,471
My "type"?

436
00:23:11,265 --> 00:23:12,850
He may seem like a good man,

437
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:15,185
but don't be fooled by his appearance.

438
00:23:16,270 --> 00:23:17,479
He's totally two-faced.

439
00:23:17,563 --> 00:23:20,941
He's the type to smile
while stabbing you in the back.

440
00:23:24,737 --> 00:23:27,531
Bull's-eye!

441
00:23:32,286 --> 00:23:35,205
The Crown Prince must have been
born with a divine gift for archery.

442
00:23:35,289 --> 00:23:37,249
Every shot he takes is a bull's-eye.

443
00:23:39,877 --> 00:23:42,129
- It's a pheasant!
- Look, a pheasant!

444
00:23:47,343 --> 00:23:50,137
Bull's-eye!

445
00:23:50,220 --> 00:23:52,222
Did His Highness hit the pheasant?

446
00:23:52,306 --> 00:23:53,641
That is not all he can hit.

447
00:23:53,724 --> 00:23:56,560
He hunts any wild animal
that roams near the rear garden.

448
00:23:59,313 --> 00:24:00,439
Wild animals?

449
00:24:10,658 --> 00:24:11,825
Go away!

450
00:24:12,326 --> 00:24:14,036
Run far away from the palace!

451
00:24:17,498 --> 00:24:18,457
Go!

452
00:24:19,208 --> 00:24:21,210
Do not ever come near here again.

453
00:24:21,794 --> 00:24:22,836
Go!

454
00:25:02,918 --> 00:25:04,920
Just because you act all high and mighty

455
00:25:05,004 --> 00:25:07,923
doesn't mean you suddenly gain authority.

456
00:25:08,757 --> 00:25:11,051
True charisma…

457
00:25:12,553 --> 00:25:14,096
comes from actual ability…

458
00:25:15,472 --> 00:25:16,807
you know what I mean?

459
00:25:16,890 --> 00:25:17,766
All right.

460
00:25:17,850 --> 00:25:19,768
Seeing how you so openly speak ill of him,

461
00:25:19,852 --> 00:25:21,729
it seems you two are on poor terms.

462
00:25:22,229 --> 00:25:24,064
He will certainly never visit.

463
00:25:24,148 --> 00:25:25,315
Excellent.

464
00:25:28,027 --> 00:25:29,111
Cha Se-gye.

465
00:25:29,194 --> 00:25:31,196
I give you this dog as a gift in return.

466
00:25:31,697 --> 00:25:33,907
I do not have the money
to buy luxury goods,

467
00:25:33,991 --> 00:25:35,409
and I have no letter for you,

468
00:25:35,492 --> 00:25:37,244
so I shall entrust this dog to you.

469
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:40,998
Think of him as an extension of me,
and take good care of him.

470
00:25:41,081 --> 00:25:42,750
Are you nuts? Why would I…

471
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:48,589
This dog will be more comfortable
in your home than in my windowless one.

472
00:25:48,672 --> 00:25:49,757
Here.

473
00:25:50,466 --> 00:25:52,801
I am counting on you, Cha Se-gye.

474
00:25:59,475 --> 00:26:00,392
Hey!

475
00:26:00,893 --> 00:26:02,186
Hey, Shin Seo-ri!

476
00:26:02,895 --> 00:26:04,605
I'm allergic to dogs!

477
00:26:05,731 --> 00:26:06,607
Hey!

478
00:26:07,733 --> 00:26:08,901
Damn it.

479
00:26:09,568 --> 00:26:11,570
Stop wagging your tail. You're shedding.

480
00:26:12,446 --> 00:26:14,114
When was your last bath?

481
00:26:16,658 --> 00:26:17,868
You stink.

482
00:26:19,787 --> 00:26:21,497
You're so loud. Be quiet.

483
00:26:22,206 --> 00:26:24,291
Quiet! Be quiet!

484
00:26:30,297 --> 00:26:33,509
Anyway, you'll be out of here by tomorrow.

485
00:26:36,011 --> 00:26:37,346
I have fur all over me.

486
00:26:40,140 --> 00:26:41,391
God, it's so itchy.

487
00:26:41,475 --> 00:26:43,143
So itchy. Damn it.

488
00:26:43,227 --> 00:26:45,354
Seriously? All because
of that crazy woman.

489
00:26:46,313 --> 00:26:47,815
Damn it.

490
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:50,067
Should I just kick it out now?

491
00:26:50,150 --> 00:26:51,193
What?

492
00:26:51,819 --> 00:26:53,153
You kicked the dog out?

493
00:26:53,779 --> 00:26:55,489
A man who poisons everything he touches.

494
00:26:55,572 --> 00:26:57,991
A thousand cuts and being torn limb
from limb would not suffice!

495
00:26:58,075 --> 00:27:00,661
May you rot and die a painful death!

496
00:27:08,335 --> 00:27:09,670
Damn it.

497
00:27:09,753 --> 00:27:12,589
Even just imagining it makes me sick.

498
00:27:14,049 --> 00:27:17,344
God only knows what she'd do to me
if I just dumped it somewhere.

499
00:27:19,138 --> 00:27:21,014
I should get rid of it properly.

500
00:27:28,814 --> 00:27:30,023
Living alone must get lonely.

501
00:27:30,107 --> 00:27:32,234
It's a gift for you. Take it.

502
00:27:32,317 --> 00:27:33,193
Thank you so much.

503
00:27:33,277 --> 00:27:35,028
It's a bit too dirty for a gift.

504
00:27:35,112 --> 00:27:36,321
Then consider it a mission.

505
00:27:36,405 --> 00:27:37,781
Just get it out of my sight.

506
00:27:37,865 --> 00:27:40,659
You're allergic to dog fur.
Why did you bring it home?

507
00:27:41,535 --> 00:27:44,121
You can clearly tell it's a stray.

508
00:27:44,204 --> 00:27:46,415
I didn't find it. Someone forced it on me.

509
00:27:46,498 --> 00:27:49,126
But you're not one to be saddled
with something against your will.

510
00:27:49,209 --> 00:27:50,752
- Who was it?
- You don't need to know.

511
00:27:50,836 --> 00:27:53,005
Anyway, get rid of this dog today.

512
00:27:54,047 --> 00:27:55,507
Or just raise it yourself.

513
00:27:56,258 --> 00:27:58,093
Sir, I can't take the dog either.

514
00:27:58,177 --> 00:28:00,429
My Min-ji is very picky.

515
00:28:03,807 --> 00:28:05,142
Min-ji?

516
00:28:05,225 --> 00:28:06,560
Is Min-ji your girlfriend?

517
00:28:06,643 --> 00:28:08,312
Min-ji is the name of my cat.

518
00:28:08,395 --> 00:28:09,980
You wouldn't know
because you don't care,

519
00:28:10,063 --> 00:28:11,732
but I've been a cat owner for ten years.

520
00:28:11,815 --> 00:28:13,108
Then find it a home.

521
00:28:13,192 --> 00:28:15,110
Pets are popular these days, right?

522
00:28:15,194 --> 00:28:18,071
Well, the chances of a full-grown,
mixed-breed dog like this

523
00:28:18,155 --> 00:28:20,699
- getting adopted aren't good.
- So what should I do?

524
00:28:20,782 --> 00:28:22,367
You want me to continue living with it?

525
00:28:22,451 --> 00:28:25,787
You poor thing.
Of all people, he had to find you.

526
00:28:30,167 --> 00:28:32,294
I arranged this gathering
to mark a new beginning.

527
00:28:32,377 --> 00:28:34,338
As a family, we should clear the air.

528
00:28:34,421 --> 00:28:35,714
What is there to eat?

529
00:28:35,797 --> 00:28:38,050
This is practically an empty plate.

530
00:28:38,133 --> 00:28:39,885
Such poor hospitality. My goodness.

531
00:28:52,272 --> 00:28:53,315
Why, this is

532
00:28:53,398 --> 00:28:54,983
the ultimate land-and-sea delicacy

533
00:28:55,067 --> 00:28:56,985
where the vitality
freshly drawn from the ocean

534
00:28:57,069 --> 00:28:59,154
is combined with the spirit of Mount Jiri

535
00:28:59,219 --> 00:29:00,928
to achieve a sublime harmony of opposites.

536
00:29:01,021 --> 00:29:03,450
DIVINE FLAVORS

537
00:29:03,533 --> 00:29:06,453
It seems our Seo-ri
has a real knack for mukbang.

538
00:29:06,536 --> 00:29:08,538
We should get you on a food show too.

539
00:29:09,248 --> 00:29:10,958
"Our Seo-ri"? Since when?

540
00:29:11,041 --> 00:29:13,085
Oh, right. Director Kim called yesterday.

541
00:29:13,168 --> 00:29:16,004
You've been cast
in The Women's Kingdom Season 2.

542
00:29:16,088 --> 00:29:19,049
Since it's a new season,
they said they needed a new face.

543
00:29:19,132 --> 00:29:20,759
So I got you a spot, Seo-ri.

544
00:29:21,426 --> 00:29:23,679
Ma'am. How could you make
such a decision

545
00:29:23,762 --> 00:29:24,763
without even telling me?

546
00:29:24,846 --> 00:29:28,392
Why would I need to consult you
for a minor supporting role?

547
00:29:28,976 --> 00:29:30,310
Are you done?

548
00:29:30,394 --> 00:29:32,312
That yellow part was the most delicious.

549
00:29:32,396 --> 00:29:33,397
You eat it.

550
00:29:35,023 --> 00:29:36,275
Then I will not refuse.

551
00:29:38,652 --> 00:29:40,195
My, you have a healthy appetite.

552
00:29:40,279 --> 00:29:41,488
So healthy.

553
00:29:53,625 --> 00:29:55,335
Quality over quantity, I see.

554
00:29:55,419 --> 00:29:58,422
I must succeed
so I can eat that for every meal.

555
00:30:01,258 --> 00:30:02,259
NEW MESSAGE

556
00:30:06,471 --> 00:30:08,807
Binge-watch Season 1 before the meeting.

557
00:30:08,890 --> 00:30:12,060
While you're at it,
analyze the trends of other hit shows.

558
00:30:12,144 --> 00:30:14,771
You're probably rusty
after your long break.

559
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:18,317
How could I even be rusty
when I am just getting started?

560
00:30:19,359 --> 00:30:21,153
Seeing is believing, I suppose.

561
00:30:21,236 --> 00:30:22,863
Hey! Seriously.

562
00:30:22,946 --> 00:30:24,740
You're talking over Ji-hyo.

563
00:30:24,823 --> 00:30:26,366
Please be quiet.

564
00:30:27,534 --> 00:30:29,661
You have turned to stone
in that very spot.

565
00:30:30,454 --> 00:30:31,830
Is it that entertaining?

566
00:30:32,456 --> 00:30:34,916
There's nothing like a drama
to escape reality.

567
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,668
Your reality seems pretty tough too.

568
00:30:36,752 --> 00:30:38,045
Maybe you should binge-watch it.

569
00:30:38,128 --> 00:30:41,173
I saw her playing the queen.
Her acting was insufferably vulgar.

570
00:30:43,008 --> 00:30:45,177
What do you know about acting?

571
00:30:54,686 --> 00:30:55,729
Jeez.

572
00:31:06,531 --> 00:31:07,783
Unit 203?

573
00:31:17,667 --> 00:31:21,296
My, this "binge-watching" business
is truly captivating.

574
00:31:21,380 --> 00:31:25,133
Once you start,
you forget to even eat or drink.

575
00:31:25,884 --> 00:31:26,802
…PALACE INTRIGUES

576
00:31:26,885 --> 00:31:27,761
ASSASSINATIONS…

577
00:31:27,844 --> 00:31:29,679
Did you need to go this hard?

578
00:31:29,763 --> 00:31:31,848
Besides binge-watching,

579
00:31:31,932 --> 00:31:34,434
I was told to analyze "the trends."

580
00:31:36,353 --> 00:31:38,063
Is there anything else?

581
00:31:38,146 --> 00:31:39,272
No?

582
00:31:40,399 --> 00:31:42,609
SANDGLASS

583
00:31:42,692 --> 00:31:44,486
I thought I could have you this way.

584
00:31:44,569 --> 00:31:45,737
- Jeez.
- You're my woman.

585
00:31:45,821 --> 00:31:48,031
He really does not understand women.

586
00:31:48,115 --> 00:31:50,158
He would scare away any woman.

587
00:31:50,242 --> 00:31:51,993
Impotent?

588
00:31:52,077 --> 00:31:54,079
How could I be impotent?

589
00:31:54,162 --> 00:31:55,789
- "Impotent."
- What are you talking about?

590
00:31:55,872 --> 00:31:57,833
- "Impotent!"
- How could I be impotent?

591
00:31:58,458 --> 00:32:00,710
How? How could I be impotent?

592
00:32:00,794 --> 00:32:02,629
As if being impotent was a big deal.

593
00:32:03,171 --> 00:32:06,842
The eunuchs could not fool around,
but they lived large and lavishly.

594
00:32:06,925 --> 00:32:08,552
LADIES OF THE PALACE

595
00:32:08,635 --> 00:32:11,012
You went between the Queen
and the concubines

596
00:32:11,096 --> 00:32:12,973
to intentionally sow discord?

597
00:32:20,939 --> 00:32:23,275
It has been ages since I heard
such a gratifying thrashing.

598
00:32:23,358 --> 00:32:25,235
It is simply music to my ears!

599
00:32:26,027 --> 00:32:27,362
There you go.

600
00:32:27,446 --> 00:32:28,864
She's actually laughing at that.

601
00:32:28,947 --> 00:32:30,657
You are amazing!

602
00:32:31,491 --> 00:32:32,617
My goodness.

603
00:32:36,621 --> 00:32:39,708
Since that obstinate man even took in
Young Master Dog,

604
00:32:39,791 --> 00:32:42,335
I shall take this chance
to properly thank him.

605
00:32:52,095 --> 00:32:54,556
Hey, Unit 203. You know your hanja.

606
00:32:54,639 --> 00:32:57,142
I happen to be quite gifted
in classical verse.

607
00:32:58,935 --> 00:33:02,397
Wait. "One…" Gosh.

608
00:33:02,939 --> 00:33:04,065
Who is this for anyway?

609
00:33:04,149 --> 00:33:06,276
As my funds for luxury goods are lacking,

610
00:33:06,359 --> 00:33:09,988
I intend to give this handwritten letter
to my fan as a gift in reverse.

611
00:33:10,071 --> 00:33:11,323
A fan?

612
00:33:11,406 --> 00:33:13,909
I thought you were unknown.
You have a fan now?

613
00:33:13,992 --> 00:33:17,287
Of course. Se-gye is the only one
who worries about me.

614
00:33:23,317 --> 00:33:24,957
That concludes the contract signing.

615
00:33:25,044 --> 00:33:26,671
Once the remaining purchase balance

616
00:33:26,755 --> 00:33:28,798
and Ms. Shin's signing bonus
are deposited,

617
00:33:28,882 --> 00:33:30,425
you will officially become a subsidiary.

618
00:33:30,509 --> 00:33:32,636
Let's get this project moving quickly.

619
00:33:32,719 --> 00:33:35,597
The marketing team will send over
the ad proposal this week,

620
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:37,140
so give us your feedback right away.

621
00:33:37,224 --> 00:33:38,934
Yes, of course.

622
00:33:40,101 --> 00:33:41,394
Wait, Mr. Cha.

623
00:33:41,478 --> 00:33:43,855
Will we be taking a commemorative photo?

624
00:33:43,939 --> 00:33:45,023
- A photo?
- Yes.

625
00:33:46,316 --> 00:33:49,110
Okay, say cheese. One, two, three.

626
00:33:51,571 --> 00:33:52,656
Good work, everyone.

627
00:33:53,406 --> 00:33:55,700
Well, you must be very busy.

628
00:34:10,674 --> 00:34:11,967
Shin Seo-ri, what now?

629
00:34:15,303 --> 00:34:17,639
You knew it was me just from my footsteps?

630
00:34:18,974 --> 00:34:20,433
You have a serious problem.

631
00:34:21,059 --> 00:34:23,061
What now? What do you want?

632
00:34:26,893 --> 00:34:28,619
You have been sniffling since earlier.

633
00:34:28,694 --> 00:34:31,278
Is your body not hardy enough
to avoid a measly little cold?

634
00:34:31,361 --> 00:34:33,280
Thanks to a certain someone, I'm a mess.

635
00:34:33,363 --> 00:34:35,240
I've had a runny nose
for over a week now.

636
00:34:35,323 --> 00:34:36,199
Yes.

637
00:34:36,700 --> 00:34:38,451
As it is, I owe you a great deal.

638
00:34:38,535 --> 00:34:41,079
So I wanted to take this chance
to thank you properly.

639
00:34:42,872 --> 00:34:44,624
Here, take it.

640
00:34:45,333 --> 00:34:46,751
What's this? A legal notice?

641
00:34:46,835 --> 00:34:48,128
A missive.

642
00:34:48,211 --> 00:34:49,713
I mean, a handwritten letter.

643
00:34:51,673 --> 00:34:52,841
- A letter?
- Yes.

644
00:34:52,924 --> 00:34:54,134
For me?

645
00:34:57,178 --> 00:34:59,764
It is a letter expressing my gratitude,

646
00:34:59,848 --> 00:35:02,851
so be sure to read it alone tonight
before you go to sleep.

647
00:35:23,705 --> 00:35:25,874
It really is a missive. Hanja and all.

648
00:35:29,753 --> 00:35:30,837
"Jak."

649
00:35:33,214 --> 00:35:34,841
Is she messing with me? Damn it.

650
00:35:52,150 --> 00:35:54,069
How did you fare last night?

651
00:35:55,236 --> 00:35:58,948
By a sunlit window,
my fondness for you grows.

652
00:36:00,075 --> 00:36:03,411
If the traces of my visits in your dreams
were left as a fragrance,

653
00:36:04,454 --> 00:36:08,124
the green garden before your door
would be full of butterflies.

654
00:36:08,208 --> 00:36:10,168
What does this even mean?

655
00:36:13,797 --> 00:36:16,007
Someone might mistake this
for a love letter.

656
00:36:25,767 --> 00:36:27,477
Hey! You little son of a…

657
00:36:29,688 --> 00:36:31,940
Is it because
you're from the streets?

658
00:36:32,023 --> 00:36:34,651
You try to snatch
anything that drops to the floor.

659
00:36:34,734 --> 00:36:36,778
You'll get a tummy ache, you punk.

660
00:36:37,570 --> 00:36:39,531
Damn it. Gross.

661
00:37:03,179 --> 00:37:04,931
"Amazing."

662
00:37:06,725 --> 00:37:08,017
MY AMAZING FAN

663
00:37:08,643 --> 00:37:09,728
"My…"

664
00:37:12,564 --> 00:37:13,732
"My man"?

665
00:37:19,612 --> 00:37:21,781
"My…

666
00:37:23,366 --> 00:37:24,701
amazing…

667
00:37:25,869 --> 00:37:26,995
fan."

668
00:37:27,078 --> 00:37:28,496
"My man"?

669
00:37:44,262 --> 00:37:45,972
This woman is in love with me.

670
00:38:01,529 --> 00:38:03,031
My goodness.

671
00:38:03,114 --> 00:38:05,533
What an incredible view.

672
00:38:05,617 --> 00:38:07,243
You have a job now.

673
00:38:07,327 --> 00:38:09,829
Why stay in that windowless room
any longer?

674
00:38:09,913 --> 00:38:12,540
You have the deposit money now,
and the rent will be the same.

675
00:38:12,624 --> 00:38:15,418
Not to mention, you'll have
the whole floor to yourself.

676
00:38:15,502 --> 00:38:18,421
Absolutely.
A place like this is a total steal.

677
00:38:18,505 --> 00:38:19,672
A total steal.

678
00:38:19,756 --> 00:38:21,466
The view is quite refreshing.

679
00:38:21,549 --> 00:38:22,509
This will do.

680
00:38:23,134 --> 00:38:24,469
Even a yard to run around in.

681
00:38:24,552 --> 00:38:25,804
A new residence

682
00:38:25,887 --> 00:38:28,306
calls for a proper ritual.
It has been a while.

683
00:38:31,476 --> 00:38:33,311
Regarding the first draft
of the Dynaestie ad,

684
00:38:33,394 --> 00:38:34,938
her agency's response has been positive.

685
00:38:35,021 --> 00:38:37,315
A few details need tweaking
before it goes to the ad agency,

686
00:38:37,398 --> 00:38:40,193
but we should be able to see a preview
by the end of the month.

687
00:38:40,276 --> 00:38:41,528
Okay.

688
00:38:42,946 --> 00:38:44,072
Hey, Mr. Son.

689
00:38:45,573 --> 00:38:48,076
Have you ever received a love letter?

690
00:38:48,159 --> 00:38:49,494
A love letter?

691
00:38:50,203 --> 00:38:52,121
I've been dumped plenty of times.

692
00:38:52,205 --> 00:38:54,457
Wait, I got a note from a Secret Santa

693
00:38:54,958 --> 00:38:55,875
in elementary school.

694
00:38:55,959 --> 00:38:57,043
No, not like that.

695
00:38:57,126 --> 00:39:00,380
I mean a handwritten letter.
One that the sender personally wrote.

696
00:39:02,757 --> 00:39:03,967
Why do you ask?

697
00:39:04,801 --> 00:39:07,053
Did someone profess their love for you?

698
00:39:07,136 --> 00:39:08,388
No.

699
00:39:08,471 --> 00:39:09,556
Of course not.

700
00:39:09,639 --> 00:39:11,641
When did I say that?

701
00:39:11,724 --> 00:39:12,642
I'm just curious.

702
00:39:12,725 --> 00:39:14,227
And why are you so curious?

703
00:39:14,310 --> 00:39:17,272
I need to know why you're asking
so I can answer properly.

704
00:39:17,355 --> 00:39:18,857
Just because.

705
00:39:19,524 --> 00:39:22,819
I was wondering what the intention is
when people give love letters.

706
00:39:22,902 --> 00:39:25,905
There's no hidden intention.
They're just sharing how they feel.

707
00:39:28,241 --> 00:39:29,367
Feelings.

708
00:39:29,450 --> 00:39:30,910
Not everything in this world

709
00:39:30,994 --> 00:39:33,204
has dark ulterior motives

710
00:39:33,288 --> 00:39:35,164
and conspiracies lurking underneath.

711
00:39:35,248 --> 00:39:36,541
This world

712
00:39:36,624 --> 00:39:39,252
is far more filled with humanity
than you think, sir.

713
00:39:40,336 --> 00:39:44,007
So what? Are you saying
I always have dark ulterior motives?

714
00:39:52,015 --> 00:39:54,434
How long must I handle
these menial tasks myself?

715
00:39:54,517 --> 00:39:56,477
My graceful hands are getting calluses.

716
00:39:57,770 --> 00:40:00,440
Delicate jade hands are
the very foundation of refinement.

717
00:40:00,523 --> 00:40:02,025
I need to start taking care of them.

718
00:40:03,568 --> 00:40:04,527
Damn it.

719
00:40:13,953 --> 00:40:16,164
This should be good enough
to bring a dog home.

720
00:40:16,247 --> 00:40:17,999
SHRINE OF DOG

721
00:40:26,049 --> 00:40:27,133
Hey, Unit 203.

722
00:40:27,216 --> 00:40:28,426
I mean, Rooftop.

723
00:40:28,509 --> 00:40:31,429
Why aren't you answering your phone? Huh?

724
00:40:31,512 --> 00:40:33,389
- What is that?
- Jeez.

725
00:40:33,473 --> 00:40:35,683
Your grandmother must be busy.

726
00:40:35,767 --> 00:40:37,602
She had it delivered this time.

727
00:40:38,269 --> 00:40:41,105
I brought it up so it wouldn't go bad.

728
00:40:41,856 --> 00:40:43,816
SENDER: NAM OK-SUN

729
00:40:55,703 --> 00:40:57,789
Seo-ri, you got the storyboard, right?

730
00:40:57,872 --> 00:40:59,499
The concept is very avant-garde,

731
00:40:59,582 --> 00:41:00,500
and it's got

732
00:41:00,583 --> 00:41:03,336
that trendy Gen Z style.
It's kitschy and well-executed.

733
00:41:03,419 --> 00:41:05,004
Mr. Cha has good taste.

734
00:41:05,088 --> 00:41:09,050
The shooting schedule will be out soon,
so really focus on your skincare regimen.

735
00:41:09,133 --> 00:41:12,095
There are so many great options now.
Glutathione shots, whitening injections.

736
00:41:12,178 --> 00:41:14,222
What is there to take special care of?

737
00:41:14,305 --> 00:41:15,807
I was born with flawless skin.

738
00:41:15,890 --> 00:41:18,685
Put the same fire you came at me with
into your skincare.

739
00:41:18,768 --> 00:41:22,105
And you're booked for Jane Asks,
the YouTube show, on the day of the shoot.

740
00:41:22,188 --> 00:41:24,983
Play up the sob story about your hardships
as an unknown actress.

741
00:41:25,066 --> 00:41:27,485
Pile on the sorrow and sentiment
to make it a tearjerker.

742
00:41:34,117 --> 00:41:35,660
But I do not know anything

743
00:41:36,577 --> 00:41:38,079
about this woman.

744
00:41:47,005 --> 00:41:49,382
NAM OK-SUN
17 YEONSOLRO 8-GIL, SONGJIN

745
00:41:56,222 --> 00:41:59,851
Sir, your cough has been bad lately.
Are you taking medicine?

746
00:41:59,934 --> 00:42:01,436
Medicine for a little cough?

747
00:42:02,603 --> 00:42:04,856
It's an issue
you could resolve quite quickly.

748
00:42:05,606 --> 00:42:08,109
Sir, that's already been taken care of.

749
00:42:11,070 --> 00:42:12,363
I posted online,

750
00:42:12,447 --> 00:42:14,532
and the dog's owner called right away.

751
00:42:15,992 --> 00:42:17,118
Really? That's great.

752
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:19,454
Secretary Kim should be returning it
to the owner now.

753
00:42:19,537 --> 00:42:21,789
You can sleep peacefully starting tonight.

754
00:42:22,707 --> 00:42:23,624
Already?

755
00:42:23,708 --> 00:42:26,919
The sooner we send it off,
the sooner your suffering ends.

756
00:42:27,003 --> 00:42:30,339
I hired cleaners to remove
every single trace.

757
00:42:30,882 --> 00:42:31,799
So don't worry.

758
00:42:31,883 --> 00:42:33,468
I'm so grateful.

759
00:42:34,886 --> 00:42:36,054
You know me.

760
00:42:37,764 --> 00:42:39,057
She's going to miss it.

761
00:42:43,519 --> 00:42:45,346
THE CHAIL SONGJIN RESORT
GROUNDBREAKING CEREMONY

762
00:42:45,496 --> 00:42:46,697
- Gosh. Chairman.
- Hey.

763
00:42:46,780 --> 00:42:48,490
- Welcome, sir.
- Thank you for your hard work.

764
00:42:48,549 --> 00:42:49,984
- Thank you.
- Hang in there.

765
00:42:50,068 --> 00:42:51,903
Thank you for working so hard.

766
00:42:51,986 --> 00:42:52,945
Oh, my.

767
00:42:53,029 --> 00:42:54,822
Did Father seriously bring him here?

768
00:42:55,573 --> 00:42:56,783
Is he going senile?

769
00:42:56,866 --> 00:42:58,618
They say time waits for no one.

770
00:42:58,701 --> 00:43:01,496
Even after all the trouble he caused,
he still dotes on his own blood.

771
00:43:01,579 --> 00:43:04,373
Ladies, people can overhear you.
You should be more careful.

772
00:43:04,457 --> 00:43:06,417
Mun-do, you seem pretty relaxed.

773
00:43:06,510 --> 00:43:09,087
Even after seeing this,
you can still be calm and philosophical?

774
00:43:09,170 --> 00:43:11,672
Come on, sis.
Have you ever seen Mun-do get angry?

775
00:43:11,756 --> 00:43:13,091
Why would I be angry?

776
00:43:13,800 --> 00:43:15,802
Especially when Uncle is so happy.

777
00:43:17,428 --> 00:43:20,223
Gosh, I really can't figure him out.

778
00:43:20,765 --> 00:43:22,642
Is he actually happy or just pretending?

779
00:43:22,725 --> 00:43:26,229
We will now break ground
for The Chail Songjin Resort.

780
00:43:27,021 --> 00:43:29,398
One, two, three!

781
00:43:29,482 --> 00:43:30,710
CHAIL E&amp;C, SONGJIN CITY…

782
00:43:33,903 --> 00:43:36,155
Please join me in a warm round of applause

783
00:43:36,239 --> 00:43:40,201
for Songjin City, Chail Resort,
and their bright futures.

784
00:43:42,995 --> 00:43:45,039
Thank you for always looking out for us.

785
00:43:45,123 --> 00:43:46,582
- It's my pleasure.
- Thank you.

786
00:43:46,666 --> 00:43:49,293
- Thank you so much.
- Once this project is completed…

787
00:43:49,377 --> 00:43:51,045
- Yes.
- …we'll have you back.

788
00:43:51,129 --> 00:43:52,713
- Thank you.
- By any chance,

789
00:43:53,339 --> 00:43:55,341
does that older brother of yours

790
00:43:55,424 --> 00:43:56,884
visit your home often?

791
00:43:56,968 --> 00:43:58,719
- Thank you.
- I look forward to it.

792
00:43:58,803 --> 00:44:00,429
Oh, my.

793
00:44:00,513 --> 00:44:02,348
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much.

794
00:44:04,058 --> 00:44:06,018
- I have high hopes.
- Exactly.

795
00:44:12,859 --> 00:44:16,279
So you go around meeting
aspiring starlets now?

796
00:44:17,029 --> 00:44:19,615
I have A-list stars
lining up for me as it is.

797
00:44:19,699 --> 00:44:21,033
What would I do with a starlet?

798
00:44:22,118 --> 00:44:23,327
Right?

799
00:44:24,829 --> 00:44:27,081
Mind your personal affairs carefully.

800
00:44:27,165 --> 00:44:29,250
Don't throw away everything you've built.

801
00:44:29,876 --> 00:44:31,210
Se-gye.

802
00:44:31,294 --> 00:44:34,005
Don't waste your time meddling.
Just focus on smiling.

803
00:44:34,088 --> 00:44:36,048
The only thing you've got going for you

804
00:44:36,132 --> 00:44:39,177
is the handsome face
you got from your mom.

805
00:44:39,260 --> 00:44:40,553
You know?

806
00:44:43,681 --> 00:44:45,433
- We'll be counting on you.
- Of course.

807
00:44:46,517 --> 00:44:49,228
- Congratulations, President Choi.
- Your first dig.

808
00:44:49,979 --> 00:44:51,522
Thank you so much for coming.

809
00:44:55,568 --> 00:44:57,111
What the hell?

810
00:44:58,279 --> 00:44:59,363
Hey.

811
00:45:01,365 --> 00:45:02,575
Watch your mouth

812
00:45:02,658 --> 00:45:04,493
before I smash that jaw of yours.

813
00:45:13,252 --> 00:45:16,297
SONGJIN CITY WELCOMES CHAIL RESORT!

814
00:45:19,008 --> 00:45:21,802
SEORI'S NOODLE SHOP

815
00:45:21,928 --> 00:45:23,262
OPEN

816
00:46:01,968 --> 00:46:04,178
Well, this feels a bit…

817
00:46:08,099 --> 00:46:09,141
Goodness me.

818
00:46:10,434 --> 00:46:11,435
Seo-ri!

819
00:46:11,519 --> 00:46:13,104
Oh my gosh, Seo-ri! You're here.

820
00:46:13,187 --> 00:46:14,605
Come here, my sweet girl.

821
00:46:15,189 --> 00:46:16,565
You're really here.

822
00:46:17,316 --> 00:46:18,276
Let me look at you.

823
00:46:18,359 --> 00:46:20,361
Why are you so skinny?

824
00:46:20,444 --> 00:46:22,738
I can't believe my sweet girl is here.

825
00:46:25,533 --> 00:46:29,370
If you'd called ahead,
I would've grilled some meat.

826
00:46:39,005 --> 00:46:41,841
The neighborhood looks deserted.
Everything is closed down.

827
00:46:43,092 --> 00:46:44,218
How is business?

828
00:46:44,302 --> 00:46:47,221
They say they're building some resort.

829
00:46:47,305 --> 00:46:49,932
Everyone just sold out
for a handful of cash.

830
00:46:50,558 --> 00:46:51,851
Just forget it.

831
00:46:52,560 --> 00:46:55,146
If they are offering you money,
you should sell too.

832
00:46:55,229 --> 00:46:56,856
- This work must be hard.
- Gosh.

833
00:46:56,939 --> 00:47:00,276
Why would I? I'm still perfectly healthy.

834
00:47:00,359 --> 00:47:02,194
I'll work as long as my body lets me.

835
00:47:02,278 --> 00:47:04,280
At my age, not working is like being dead.

836
00:47:05,239 --> 00:47:06,198
This here

837
00:47:06,782 --> 00:47:08,200
is where I'll lay my head to rest.

838
00:47:09,035 --> 00:47:12,121
I watched you grow up here
and sent you to school.

839
00:47:14,707 --> 00:47:17,835
No other place in the world
could give me this kind of peace.

840
00:47:17,918 --> 00:47:19,795
I mean, money isn't everything.

841
00:47:22,006 --> 00:47:23,507
It was just the two of them.

842
00:47:25,009 --> 00:47:27,428
They never had any need
for worldly possessions.

843
00:47:28,971 --> 00:47:30,431
Eat.

844
00:47:30,514 --> 00:47:32,141
This is needless meddling.

845
00:47:35,728 --> 00:47:36,771
Get a grip.

846
00:47:38,397 --> 00:47:40,066
Just look out for yourself.

847
00:47:41,067 --> 00:47:42,735
I have this interview

848
00:47:42,818 --> 00:47:44,987
- coming up, you see.
- Okay.

849
00:47:45,071 --> 00:47:47,406
I have to tell them
stories about my hardships

850
00:47:47,490 --> 00:47:48,866
and the pain of being a nobody.

851
00:47:48,949 --> 00:47:50,034
Stuff like that.

852
00:47:50,117 --> 00:47:51,702
Are you going to be on TV?

853
00:47:52,203 --> 00:47:53,954
What channel will it be on?

854
00:47:54,038 --> 00:47:56,207
I'll have to record that, you know?

855
00:47:56,290 --> 00:47:59,043
My childhood memories are a little hazy.

856
00:48:00,586 --> 00:48:02,004
What? You…

857
00:48:02,588 --> 00:48:04,632
don't remember your childhood?

858
00:48:05,466 --> 00:48:06,967
Well, you know,

859
00:48:07,551 --> 00:48:10,179
a lot of people forget
their childhood as they grow up.

860
00:48:10,262 --> 00:48:14,392
Come to think of it,
you have been talking strangely lately.

861
00:48:15,601 --> 00:48:19,688
You were the same way
after that accident when you almost died.

862
00:48:21,065 --> 00:48:22,525
Maybe you're sick again?

863
00:48:24,276 --> 00:48:25,403
Accident?

864
00:48:26,779 --> 00:48:28,739
Granny, we're back.

865
00:48:29,824 --> 00:48:31,659
Smells so good in here.

866
00:48:31,742 --> 00:48:32,743
Yeah.

867
00:48:36,622 --> 00:48:39,166
What did Mun-do say
to make you punch him?

868
00:48:39,250 --> 00:48:41,752
You'd better speak up
if you're hoping for any leniency.

869
00:48:41,836 --> 00:48:44,213
His face just pissed me off,
so I punched him.

870
00:48:45,005 --> 00:48:47,383
No matter how much you dislike him,
Mun-do is still our blood.

871
00:48:47,466 --> 00:48:49,343
Even with this resort project,

872
00:48:49,427 --> 00:48:52,054
there's a headache of a restaurant
standing in the way.

873
00:48:52,680 --> 00:48:54,640
Yes. That's it. That restaurant.

874
00:48:55,284 --> 00:48:56,898
Some old lady is refusing to budge.

875
00:48:56,978 --> 00:48:59,103
Mun-do's been working
day and night to take care of it.

876
00:48:59,186 --> 00:49:00,187
SEORI'S NOODLE SHOP

877
00:49:00,271 --> 00:49:03,107
How long are you going
to keep drifting alone like that?

878
00:49:03,190 --> 00:49:04,775
Are you never coming back?

879
00:49:06,152 --> 00:49:07,319
Now I'm even seeing things.

880
00:49:08,070 --> 00:49:09,321
What? What did you say?

881
00:49:10,698 --> 00:49:12,074
It's nothing.

882
00:49:26,630 --> 00:49:28,591
Granny, this is awful. Just awful.

883
00:49:29,216 --> 00:49:31,385
You can't run a restaurant
if you can't season.

884
00:49:35,931 --> 00:49:37,641
Even thugs live by a code.

885
00:49:37,725 --> 00:49:39,393
Wasting precious food like this?

886
00:49:40,311 --> 00:49:42,188
Were you born without parents!

887
00:49:42,271 --> 00:49:43,314
Seo-ri.

888
00:49:43,397 --> 00:49:45,483
Oh, right. She's…

889
00:49:45,566 --> 00:49:47,735
that granddaughter
who's acting in Seoul.

890
00:49:48,402 --> 00:49:50,070
Well, you're a feisty one, aren't you?

891
00:49:50,154 --> 00:49:52,114
You should help Granny understand.

892
00:49:52,198 --> 00:49:54,909
Nowadays, people hate
shameless holdouts like you.

893
00:49:54,992 --> 00:49:58,496
Hey! You think money is everything,
you rotten bastards?

894
00:49:59,497 --> 00:50:00,623
Seo-ri.

895
00:50:01,207 --> 00:50:02,750
I'll take care of this.

896
00:50:03,959 --> 00:50:05,920
Get inside, quick. Go on now.

897
00:50:06,462 --> 00:50:07,713
Now, now. Hey, Granny.

898
00:50:09,173 --> 00:50:10,758
She should know what's going on.

899
00:50:10,841 --> 00:50:12,676
She needs a reality check

900
00:50:12,760 --> 00:50:14,845
if she's still chasing
that pipe dream of acting,

901
00:50:14,929 --> 00:50:16,222
given her family situation.

902
00:50:16,931 --> 00:50:19,141
What did you just say, you bastard?

903
00:50:19,225 --> 00:50:21,143
You bastard! What did you say?

904
00:50:21,227 --> 00:50:23,229
Goodness me!

905
00:50:23,312 --> 00:50:24,396
Damn it.

906
00:50:25,189 --> 00:50:26,649
Pretty strong for an old lady.

907
00:50:26,732 --> 00:50:29,568
You got a lot of money?
Enough to pay my hospital bills? Damn it.

908
00:50:29,652 --> 00:50:32,154
Forget the money.
Let me just hold that hand.

909
00:50:32,238 --> 00:50:33,948
Still so fair. Granny's still got it.

910
00:50:34,031 --> 00:50:34,907
Hey.

911
00:50:38,827 --> 00:50:40,996
It's like you're begging for a beating.

912
00:50:43,332 --> 00:50:44,250
Damn it.

913
00:50:46,377 --> 00:50:47,294
Boss!

914
00:50:47,378 --> 00:50:48,462
- Boss!
- Boss!

915
00:50:48,546 --> 00:50:49,421
SEORI'S RUSTIC PERIOD

916
00:50:49,505 --> 00:50:50,881
- Listen up.
- Let go, damn it.

917
00:50:50,965 --> 00:50:52,550
We will never leave this place.

918
00:50:52,633 --> 00:50:55,261
And we have no intention
of bowing down to your boss.

919
00:50:56,136 --> 00:50:58,722
Because that would be the same
as bowing down to the Japanese.

920
00:50:58,806 --> 00:51:00,933
Boss? The Japanese?

921
00:51:01,016 --> 00:51:02,851
What the hell are you talking about?

922
00:51:04,853 --> 00:51:06,188
Rustic Period, Episode 18.

923
00:51:06,272 --> 00:51:08,983
The climactic episode
where Kim Du-han takes down Jebi.

924
00:51:09,483 --> 00:51:12,736
Since you all are acting just like
a bunch of street thugs,

925
00:51:13,320 --> 00:51:16,240
I, like Kim Du-han, will punish you all!

926
00:51:16,323 --> 00:51:19,076
So you're Kim Du-han now?

927
00:51:19,159 --> 00:51:20,286
Then I'm Gu Ma-jeok.

928
00:51:20,369 --> 00:51:21,579
Why, you little…

929
00:51:34,717 --> 00:51:37,261
- Boss!
- Boss!

930
00:51:37,344 --> 00:51:39,471
- Boss!
- Boss, you okay?

931
00:51:41,056 --> 00:51:43,392
What are you doing? Get her! Damn it!

932
00:52:12,755 --> 00:52:14,256
Seo-ri, he's got a knife!

933
00:52:22,598 --> 00:52:23,682
Cha Se-gye, what are you--

934
00:52:23,766 --> 00:52:25,601
Are you okay? Are you hurt anywhere?

935
00:52:26,644 --> 00:52:28,562
A cowardly sneak attack from behind?

936
00:52:29,480 --> 00:52:30,856
Why you…

937
00:52:30,939 --> 00:52:31,982
Oh, no.

938
00:52:41,909 --> 00:52:43,077
Cha Se-gye.

939
00:52:43,160 --> 00:52:45,663
Are you here because you were
worried about me again?

940
00:52:46,205 --> 00:52:47,206
No…

941
00:53:00,886 --> 00:53:02,054
Cha Se-gye.

942
00:53:02,137 --> 00:53:04,014
Did you read my handwritten letter?

943
00:53:04,098 --> 00:53:05,599
Yeah. I…

944
00:53:05,683 --> 00:53:07,226
And the dog?

945
00:53:07,309 --> 00:53:09,186
Is it eating and doing well?

946
00:53:09,853 --> 00:53:10,729
The dog?

947
00:53:11,397 --> 00:53:12,272
Yeah, it's fine.

948
00:53:12,940 --> 00:53:15,067
I have been meaning to reach out to you.

949
00:53:15,150 --> 00:53:16,151
Excellent timing.

950
00:53:16,235 --> 00:53:18,529
I've found a proper home now, you see.

951
00:53:19,279 --> 00:53:21,281
So I will no longer need to trouble you.

952
00:53:21,365 --> 00:53:22,991
I shall take the dog back.

953
00:53:23,075 --> 00:53:24,576
Well? Is that not great news?

954
00:53:29,373 --> 00:53:30,582
We found its owner.

955
00:53:31,333 --> 00:53:32,918
Turns out it wasn't a stray.

956
00:53:34,586 --> 00:53:35,587
You found its owner?

957
00:53:36,672 --> 00:53:38,382
Mr. Son posted about it online.

958
00:53:38,465 --> 00:53:39,883
Its owner came by right away.

959
00:53:41,593 --> 00:53:42,720
It's for the best.

960
00:53:42,803 --> 00:53:45,973
When I think about how much sleep
I lost over that damn dog…

961
00:53:49,184 --> 00:53:50,352
Thank you.

962
00:53:52,104 --> 00:53:52,980
What?

963
00:53:53,063 --> 00:53:55,482
I am very grateful to you.

964
00:53:55,566 --> 00:53:57,401
I know I said it in the letter,

965
00:53:57,484 --> 00:53:59,903
but I wanted to say it to you in person.

966
00:54:03,782 --> 00:54:05,951
You don't need to be so direct.

967
00:54:06,034 --> 00:54:07,703
I have met many people here,

968
00:54:07,786 --> 00:54:10,581
but you have been the kindest to me,
and I am most thankful.

969
00:54:12,166 --> 00:54:14,626
You must be the best fan in the world.

970
00:54:14,710 --> 00:54:15,836
Fan?

971
00:54:16,420 --> 00:54:17,671
What do you mean, a fan?

972
00:54:17,755 --> 00:54:19,047
Do not be embarrassed.

973
00:54:19,590 --> 00:54:21,383
I know you care about me as my fan.

974
00:54:21,467 --> 00:54:22,926
I am well aware of that fact.

975
00:54:24,136 --> 00:54:25,304
I'm a fan of who now?

976
00:54:25,387 --> 00:54:27,973
How can you say something
so egregious so easily?

977
00:54:28,056 --> 00:54:29,099
A fan?

978
00:54:29,183 --> 00:54:30,642
What's all this about?

979
00:54:30,726 --> 00:54:33,812
Grandpa, it's nothing.
Don't worry about it. You can just go.

980
00:54:33,896 --> 00:54:35,105
You're this lady's fan?

981
00:54:35,773 --> 00:54:37,983
- No--
- Who is she? Why are you her fan?

982
00:54:38,066 --> 00:54:39,193
Wealthy Man?

983
00:54:40,819 --> 00:54:43,614
Miss, how do you know my Se-gye?

984
00:54:45,949 --> 00:54:49,369
He is my one and only fan.
A very reassuring presence in my world.

985
00:54:50,037 --> 00:54:51,497
A fan? As if. No, that's not it…

986
00:54:52,122 --> 00:54:54,291
We just know each other professionally.

987
00:54:54,374 --> 00:54:55,709
But she says otherwise!

988
00:54:57,419 --> 00:54:59,588
What the hell
have you been doing out there?

989
00:54:59,671 --> 00:55:01,089
It's really not like that.

990
00:55:01,173 --> 00:55:04,176
She misunderstood after I took pity
on her and helped her out a few times.

991
00:55:04,259 --> 00:55:05,260
You pity me?

992
00:55:47,553 --> 00:55:49,054
I taught them a mighty lesson.

993
00:55:49,972 --> 00:55:51,557
They will stay away now.

994
00:55:54,268 --> 00:55:56,895
If they start lurking again,
let me know immediately.

995
00:55:57,855 --> 00:56:00,023
What's the point of raising
a granddaughter

996
00:56:00,107 --> 00:56:01,525
if not for times like these?

997
00:56:06,864 --> 00:56:07,781
I almost forgot.

998
00:56:08,824 --> 00:56:10,367
This is nothing special.

999
00:56:11,577 --> 00:56:13,161
Just some embroidered slippers.

1000
00:56:20,002 --> 00:56:21,003
Who…

1001
00:56:27,551 --> 00:56:28,510
are you?

1002
00:56:48,780 --> 00:56:49,907
Anyone home?

1003
00:57:04,588 --> 00:57:05,797
Look at this. I knew it.

1004
00:57:06,381 --> 00:57:09,092
So much for a deep cleaning.
Just sloppy at best.

1005
00:57:14,806 --> 00:57:15,933
Thank you.

1006
00:57:16,516 --> 00:57:19,144
I am very grateful to you.

1007
00:57:19,227 --> 00:57:20,854
I know I said it in the letter,

1008
00:57:20,938 --> 00:57:22,773
but I wanted to say it to you in person.

1009
00:57:24,858 --> 00:57:26,568
What does she take me for?

1010
00:57:26,652 --> 00:57:28,195
He is my one and only fan.

1011
00:57:28,278 --> 00:57:30,238
A very reassuring presence in my world.

1012
00:57:31,448 --> 00:57:33,951
Why did she have to go
and misunderstand like that?

1013
00:57:36,662 --> 00:57:38,121
It's making me feel bad.

1014
00:57:39,957 --> 00:57:41,458
You pity me?

1015
00:57:52,344 --> 00:57:54,304
Why did she have to make that face?

1016
00:57:55,097 --> 00:57:56,932
Now I'm worrying about her.

1017
00:58:01,895 --> 00:58:03,230
It's a nice view, even at night.

1018
00:58:03,313 --> 00:58:05,565
I see why your grandmother
refuses to leave.

1019
00:58:06,066 --> 00:58:07,401
What brings you here?

1020
00:58:08,026 --> 00:58:09,695
No matter how nice the view may be,

1021
00:58:09,778 --> 00:58:12,614
leaving your grandmother alone
in a place like this

1022
00:58:12,698 --> 00:58:13,740
feels wrong.

1023
00:58:14,700 --> 00:58:16,702
Closing the restaurant
and moving her somewhere nice

1024
00:58:16,785 --> 00:58:18,578
would give you peace of mind too.

1025
00:58:20,247 --> 00:58:23,291
Trying the carrot
since the stick didn't work?

1026
00:58:23,375 --> 00:58:25,502
No, that's not the main reason.

1027
00:58:26,837 --> 00:58:28,046
I came to cheer you on.

1028
00:58:28,130 --> 00:58:29,256
Cheer me on?

1029
00:58:32,384 --> 00:58:36,013
I know you and Se-gye
aren't anything yet.

1030
00:58:36,096 --> 00:58:39,016
But I think you two would make
a surprisingly good couple.

1031
00:58:41,643 --> 00:58:42,811
You came all this way,

1032
00:58:42,894 --> 00:58:45,564
this late at night, just to tell me that?

1033
00:58:45,647 --> 00:58:46,732
Ms. Shin.

1034
00:58:47,983 --> 00:58:50,277
You should be friends with Cha Se-gye.

1035
00:58:50,360 --> 00:58:52,237
Even better if you become his person.

1036
00:58:53,280 --> 00:58:55,699
And even better
if you decide to share a future.

1037
00:58:55,782 --> 00:58:58,952
If you do, then I can promise you
a real future.

1038
00:58:59,578 --> 00:59:02,372
For both you and your grandmother.

1039
00:59:03,999 --> 00:59:05,167
A life of comfort.

1040
00:59:10,130 --> 00:59:11,089
They do not

1041
00:59:11,631 --> 00:59:13,383
just share the same face.

1042
00:59:14,009 --> 00:59:16,762
They even share an affinity
for detestable antics.

1043
00:59:18,513 --> 00:59:21,266
Your Highness, I shall bring in the soup.

1044
00:59:32,444 --> 00:59:33,612
Taste it for poison.

1045
00:59:49,753 --> 00:59:51,129
How does it taste?

1046
00:59:51,880 --> 00:59:52,923
It is a nourishing soup

1047
00:59:53,006 --> 00:59:55,634
made with the beast
I just caught in the rear garden.

1048
01:00:12,692 --> 01:00:14,986
Your Highness, I deserve death.

1049
01:00:15,570 --> 01:00:17,239
Killing you now would be a waste,

1050
01:00:17,864 --> 01:00:20,158
when you will be of great use to me.

1051
01:00:23,995 --> 01:00:27,124
I hear you are the court lady
who serves as a companion

1052
01:00:27,207 --> 01:00:29,709
to my brother with the damaged eye.

1053
01:00:38,343 --> 01:00:40,345
Become my brother's lover.

1054
01:00:41,805 --> 01:00:42,806
Or even…

1055
01:00:46,017 --> 01:00:47,394
his most cherished…

1056
01:00:49,396 --> 01:00:51,273
dog would suffice.

1057
01:01:09,708 --> 01:01:10,667
Oh my gosh, Seo-ri!

1058
01:01:10,750 --> 01:01:13,420
You're here.
Come here, my sweet girl.

1059
01:01:13,503 --> 01:01:15,297
You're really here.

1060
01:01:16,715 --> 01:01:18,383
Have I ever, even once,

1061
01:01:18,967 --> 01:01:22,095
been loved unconditionally?

1062
01:01:31,563 --> 01:01:32,898
Ms. Shin.

1063
01:01:32,981 --> 01:01:34,941
You should be friends with Cha Se-gye.

1064
01:01:35,025 --> 01:01:38,403
Usefulness. Bait. Worth.

1065
01:01:39,487 --> 01:01:41,114
A life where none of that matters.

1066
01:01:41,198 --> 01:01:42,365
Where my existence

1067
01:01:43,450 --> 01:01:45,202
does not need to be justified.

1068
01:02:10,852 --> 01:02:11,895
How wretched.

1069
01:02:13,897 --> 01:02:15,482
How can life be so…

1070
01:02:25,992 --> 01:02:29,246
This should be good enough
to bring a dog home.

1071
01:02:31,206 --> 01:02:33,250
SHRINE OF DOG

1072
01:02:47,847 --> 01:02:49,808
Why did I make this stupid thing?

1073
01:03:46,656 --> 01:03:47,782
Are you crying?

1074
01:04:29,616 --> 01:04:32,869
This is the best you could find
with the signing bonus I gave you?

1075
01:04:35,121 --> 01:04:36,623
Why a rooftop of all places?

1076
01:04:41,211 --> 01:04:43,463
What kind of building has no elevator?

1077
01:04:43,546 --> 01:04:45,215
And it's so dark.

1078
01:04:47,842 --> 01:04:49,177
Why are you here?

1079
01:04:51,137 --> 01:04:53,807
I see. You came to mock me
for believing wholeheartedly

1080
01:04:53,890 --> 01:04:55,850
that you were my fan, like a fool.

1081
01:05:04,150 --> 01:05:05,151
I'm sorry.

1082
01:05:13,660 --> 01:05:15,286
Your grandmother's restaurant…

1083
01:05:16,746 --> 01:05:18,331
I'll apologize on their behalf.

1084
01:05:20,125 --> 01:05:21,501
Don't worry too much.

1085
01:05:23,378 --> 01:05:24,671
No need.

1086
01:05:25,255 --> 01:05:27,674
From now on, I shall handle
my own business. Stay out of it.

1087
01:05:27,757 --> 01:05:29,300
How can I just stay out of it

1088
01:05:29,384 --> 01:05:31,553
when you're always lingering around?

1089
01:05:32,262 --> 01:05:35,723
Even now, you're sitting here looking
all forlorn but refusing to budge, so I…

1090
01:05:42,021 --> 01:05:43,189
- So I keep--
- You.

1091
01:05:44,065 --> 01:05:45,483
Do not look at me like that.

1092
01:05:47,277 --> 01:05:49,279
- Like what?
- With that look in your eyes.

1093
01:05:49,362 --> 01:05:50,822
With eyes full of pity.

1094
01:05:52,449 --> 01:05:54,075
Do not look at me with pity.

1095
01:05:55,201 --> 01:05:57,787
- How am I looking at you--
- When you look at me that way,

1096
01:05:57,871 --> 01:05:59,956
I keep drawing the wrong conclusion.

1097
01:06:00,039 --> 01:06:03,084
You are not my fan or on my side,
but you look at me like that.

1098
01:06:03,168 --> 01:06:04,461
It makes me think…

1099
01:06:07,005 --> 01:06:07,964
I am…

1100
01:06:13,845 --> 01:06:15,889
someone you harbor affection for.

1101
01:06:17,474 --> 01:06:19,017
- Affection?
- Yes. Affection.

1102
01:06:19,559 --> 01:06:23,021
Strangers do not worry about you
and cheer you on.

1103
01:06:23,104 --> 01:06:25,231
It is not just me.
Anyone would think that.

1104
01:06:26,483 --> 01:06:27,567
Stop it.

1105
01:06:44,375 --> 01:06:45,960
What if you weren't mistaken?

1106
01:06:49,547 --> 01:06:50,924
What?

1107
01:06:51,007 --> 01:06:52,926
I see strictly in black and white.

1108
01:06:53,343 --> 01:06:54,260
Black or white.

1109
01:06:54,344 --> 01:06:56,012
Ally or enemy. Love it or hate it.

1110
01:06:56,095 --> 01:06:57,388
But you're

1111
01:06:58,056 --> 01:06:59,349
neither one nor the other.

1112
01:07:01,768 --> 01:07:03,436
You keep confusing me.

1113
01:07:12,195 --> 01:07:13,279
Then let me enlighten you.

1114
01:07:38,429 --> 01:07:40,598
See? You remain unfazed.

1115
01:07:42,767 --> 01:07:44,894
That settles it, does it not?

1116
01:07:45,478 --> 01:07:46,688
No.

1117
01:07:47,272 --> 01:07:48,565
That won't suffice.

1118
01:07:50,483 --> 01:07:52,610
- If we're checking, we check thoroughly.
- How?

1119
01:07:52,694 --> 01:07:53,861
Like this.

1120
01:08:50,501 --> 01:08:54,047
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

1121
01:09:24,151 --> 01:09:26,153
A fierce war of courtship begins.

1122
01:09:26,225 --> 01:09:28,325
It's a green light for me.
I've decided to pursue you.

1123
01:09:28,400 --> 01:09:30,541
Once your heart wavers,
you become weak.

1124
01:09:30,625 --> 01:09:33,211
In this life, I shall become
a wealthy Buddhist nun.

1125
01:09:33,294 --> 01:09:35,338
She's actually playing hard to get.

1126
01:09:35,421 --> 01:09:37,197
Most males will shower
the females with gifts.

1127
01:09:37,298 --> 01:09:38,866
"I surrender! I'll die without you!"

1128
01:09:38,966 --> 01:09:40,176
Desperately…

1129
01:09:40,259 --> 01:09:42,053
So stop being
so pathetically clingy. Jeez.

1130
01:09:42,804 --> 01:09:45,223
- Don't say no a second time. Call me.
- Have we met?

1131
01:09:45,306 --> 01:09:48,267
In this courtship battle,
will he emerge victorious?

1132
01:09:48,351 --> 01:09:50,728
Do you truly harbor affection for me?

1133
01:09:54,109 --> 01:09:56,109
Subtitle translation by Justin S. Kim
